added.description: Space Ghost marks a "special notch in the belt that is the Space Ghost saga" with returning guests Bobcat Goldthwait and Judy Tenuda. The show also includes special appearances by villian-turned-announcer Tansut and the evil Chad Ghostal, as well as a spectacular career retrospective montage compiled by Moltar.

added.description: Self-heralded "comedy ghetto" resident Michael McKean barely gets a word in with Space Ghost, and David Lander suffers a similar fate. The reason? Zorak and Space Ghost's roommate tiff spilling over into the show. In addition, a menacing "kitty" blimp hovers around Ghost Planet.
added.title: Boo Boo Kitty
tags: sgc2c space ghost coast to coast episode 45 boo boo kitty michael mckean david lander blimp

added.description: Space Ghost introduces "Space Time Quiz Fun 9000" and his "contestants," comedians David Cross and Bob Odenkirk of HBO's "Mr. Show." What follows is a rapid-fire conversation in more ways than one, as Odenkirk's growing addiction to power-band blasts results in a steady volley from Space Ghost.
added.title: Gallagher
tags: space ghost coast to coast episode 35 gallagher bob odenkirk david cross mr show

added.description: Grandpa Space Ghost, whose physique is identical to his grandson's and whose voice is identical to WCW wrestler "Macho Man" Randy Savage, gives an "OOOO-YEEAAAHHH!" performance despite being clubbed with a chair by Zorak. Grandpa Ghostal interviews kid actress Raven Symone.
added.title: Piledriver
tags: space ghost coast to coast sgc2c episode 51 piledriver macho man randy savage grandpa leonard ghostal raven symone

added.description: After revealing that contractual squabbles before the premiere of "Space Ghost Coast to Coast" resulted in an aborted test shoot starring rival superhero Birdman, host Lokar presents exclusive glimpses of this "lost" pilot.
added.title: Pilot
tags: sgc2c space ghost coast to coast episode 39 pilot lokar birdman american gladiators

added.description: This flashback episode transports viewers to a dress rehearsal two days before the premiere of "Space Ghost Coast to Coast" in April 1994. Offering a rare glimpse behind the scenes, "Rehearsal" features Space Ghost, Moltar and Zorak flubbing familiar gags, missing cues and mistiming special effects.
added.title: Rehearsal
tags: space ghost coast to coast episode 34 rehearsal flashback fred schneider moltar zorak

added.description: "Beavis and Butthead" and "King of the Hill" creator Mike Judge kindly asks Space Ghost to "whack the Rugrats." Space Ghost agrees to the job, as long as he can get onto one of Judge's shows. Harland Williams doesn't last long after calling Space Ghost "Billy" and "Naughty Space Ghost."
added.title: Sphinx
tags: space ghost coast to coast sgc2c episode 47 sphinx beavis butthead mike judge harland williams

added.description: Desperate for a new gig, Space Ghost kisses up to "Talk Soup" host John Henson and "Entertainment Tonight" host Bob Goen by telling each that they are "pretty men." Space Ghost even offers to set Henson up with his "sister" Judy. Brak spoils the affair by spilling gravy all over the set.
added.title: Suckup
tags: space ghost coast to coast sgc2c episode 52 suckup talk soup john henson bob goen

added.description: Space Ghost presents a special tribute to Zorak. Dr. Maxcy Nolan, professor of entomology at the University of Georgia, speculates that the bandleader may be hiding an extra set of legs under his vest. Exterminator Steve Arnold, meanwhile, reveals that he says "Take this!" before going after insects.
added.title: Zorak
tags: sgc2c space ghost coast to coast episode 41 zorak maxcy nolan legs steve arnold insects
